TITLE: CSS Declaration Sorter Configuration in cssnano-preset-advanced
DESCRIPTION: The configuration used for the css-declaration-sorter plugin which excludes it from processing.
SOURCE: https://github.com/cssnano/cssnano/blob/master/packages/cssnano-preset-advanced/README.md#2025-04-21_snippet_4

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
{
  exclude: true;
}
```

----------------------------------------

TITLE: Configuring individual plugins in cssnano
DESCRIPTION: This snippet illustrates various ways to configure individual plugins in cssnano. It shows how to pass plugins as strings, functions, or arrays with options, demonstrating the flexibility in plugin configuration.
SOURCE: https://github.com/cssnano/cssnano/blob/master/site/src/docs/config-file.md#2025-04-21_snippet_5

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
// cssnano.config.js
module.exports = {
  plugins: [require('autoprefixer')]

  // or
  plugins: ['autoprefixer', 'postcss-preset-env']

  // or
  plugins: [ 
    ['autoprefixer', { remove: false }],
  ]

  // or
  plugins: [
    [ require('autoprefixer'), {remove: false} ],
    [ 'postcss-preset-env']
  ]
};
```

----------------------------------------

TITLE: Configuring cssnano Advanced Preset in package.json
DESCRIPTION: JSON configuration in package.json to use the advanced preset in cssnano. This sets up the project to use advanced transforms for CSS optimization.
SOURCE: https://github.com/cssnano/cssnano/blob/master/site/src/docs/advanced-transforms.md#2025-04-21_snippet_1

LANGUAGE: json
CODE:
```
{
  "name": "awesome-application",
  "cssnano": {
    "preset": "advanced"
  }
}
```

----------------------------------------

TITLE: Configuring postcss-svgo Plugin with Custom SVGO Options
DESCRIPTION: Custom configuration for the postcss-svgo plugin that optimizes inline SVG in CSS. This configuration uses the preset-default SVGO configuration but overrides the removeViewBox option to ensure viewBox attributes are preserved in SVG elements.
SOURCE: https://github.com/cssnano/cssnano/blob/master/packages/cssnano-preset-advanced/README.md#2025-04-21_snippet_7

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
{
  plugins: [
    {
      name: 'preset-default',
      params: {
        overrides: {
          removeViewBox: false,
        },
      },
    },
  ],
}
```

----------------------------------------

TITLE: Configuring cssnano with PostCSS
DESCRIPTION: JavaScript configuration file (postcss.config.js) that sets up cssnano with default preset in PostCSS.
SOURCE: https://github.com/cssnano/cssnano/blob/master/site/src/docs/getting-started.md#2025-04-21_snippet_2

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
module.exports = {
    plugins: [
        require('cssnano')({
            preset: 'default',
        }),
    ],
};
```

----------------------------------------

TITLE: Initializing cssnano with Default Preset in postcss.config.js
DESCRIPTION: This snippet demonstrates how to load cssnano with the default preset in a postcss.config.js file. It uses the 'require' function to load cssnano and specifies the 'default' preset.
SOURCE: https://github.com/cssnano/cssnano/blob/master/site/src/docs/presets.md#2025-04-21_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
module.exports = {
    plugins: [
        require('cssnano')({
            preset: 'default',
        }),
    ],
};
```

----------------------------------------

TITLE: Disabling a plugin in cssnano preset configuration
DESCRIPTION: This snippet demonstrates how to disable a specific plugin (discardComments) when using a preset in cssnano. It shows the configuration in a JavaScript module format, which can be used in a cssnano.config.js file.
SOURCE: https://github.com/cssnano/cssnano/blob/master/site/src/docs/config-file.md#2025-04-21_snippet_3

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
// cssnano.config.js
module.exports = {
  preset: [ 
    require('cssnano-preset-default'),
    { discardComments: false } 
  ]
};
```

----------------------------------------

TITLE: Configuring cssnano with PostCSS and custom preset
DESCRIPTION: This snippet demonstrates how to configure cssnano programmatically with PostCSS, using the lite preset and adding the autoprefixer plugin. It shows how to import necessary modules, create a custom preset, and process CSS with the configuration.
SOURCE: https://github.com/cssnano/cssnano/blob/master/site/src/docs/config-file.md#2025-04-21_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
import postcss from 'postcss';
import cssnano from 'cssnano';
import litePreset from 'cssnano-preset-lite';
import autoprefixer from 'autoprefixer';
const preset = litePreset({ discardComments: false });

postcss([cssnano({ preset, plugins: [autoprefixer] })])
  .process("/* Your CSS here */");
```

----------------------------------------

TITLE: Configuring postcss-svgo Plugin in JavaScript
DESCRIPTION: Example JavaScript code showing how to configure the postcss-svgo plugin with custom SVGO options. This demonstrates disabling specific optimizations like removeViewBox and removeComments, and setting precision for numeric values.
SOURCE: https://github.com/cssnano/cssnano/blob/master/packages/postcss-svgo/README.md#2025-04-21_snippet_3

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
const postcss = require('postcss');
const svgo = require('postcss-svgo');

const opts = {
    plugins: [{
        name: 'preset-default',
        params: {
            overrides: {
                removeViewBox: false,
                removeComments: false,
                cleanupNumericValues: {
                    floatPrecision: 2
                }
            }
        }
    }]
};


postcss([ svgo(opts) ]).process(css).then((result) => {
    console.log(result.css)
});
```

----------------------------------------

TITLE: Using cssnano JavaScript API with Options
DESCRIPTION: Demonstrates the updated syntax for using cssnano's JavaScript API, showing how to pass options to both cssnano and PostCSS process methods. This reflects the change from cssnano.process() to cssnano().process().
SOURCE: https://github.com/cssnano/cssnano/blob/master/site/src/blog/2021-04-10-cssnano-5.md#2025-04-21_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
cssnano(cssnanoOptions).process(postcssOptions)
```

