TITLE: Using postcss-colormin to minify CSS colors
DESCRIPTION: Example demonstrating how to use postcss-colormin to convert rgba(255, 0, 0, 1) to the more concise 'red' color value in CSS.
SOURCE: https://github.com/cssnano/cssnano/blob/master/packages/postcss-colormin/README.md#2025-04-21_snippet_1

LANGUAGE: js
CODE:
```
var postcss = require('postcss')
var colormin = require('postcss-colormin');

var css = 'h1 {color: rgba(255, 0, 0, 1)}';
console.log(postcss(colormin()).process(css).css);

// => 'h1 {color:red}'
```

