TITLE: Using Custom Comment Removal Function with PostCSS
DESCRIPTION: Example of using a custom removal function to selectively remove comments starting with '@' character while preserving other comments.
SOURCE: https://github.com/cssnano/cssnano/blob/master/packages/postcss-discard-comments/README.md#2025-04-21_snippet_4

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
var css = '/* headings *//*@ h1 */h1{margin:0 auto}/*@ h2 */h2{color:red}';
console.log(postcss(comments({
    remove: function(comment) { return comment[0] == "@"; }
})).process(css).css);
//=> /* headings */h1{margin:0 auto}h2{color:red}
```

