TITLE: CSS Keyframes Animation with Media Queries Example 1
DESCRIPTION: Demonstrates multiple @keyframes declarations for fade-in animation with various opacity values, including media queries and support conditions. Shows both standard and webkit-prefixed versions.
SOURCE: https://github.com/cssnano/cssnano/blob/master/packages/postcss-discard-overridden/README.md#2025-04-21_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: css
CODE:
```
@-webkit-keyframes fade-in {
  0% {
    opacity: 0;
  }
  100% {
    opacity: 0.8;
  }
}
@keyframes fade-in {
  0% {
    opacity: 0;
  }
  100% {
    opacity: 0.8;
  }
}
@media (max-width: 500px) {
  @-webkit-keyframes fade-in {
    0% {
      opacity: 0;
    }
    100% {
      opacity: 1;
    }
  }
  @keyframes fade-in {
    0% {
      opacity: 0;
    }
    100% {
      opacity: 1;
    }
  }
  @-webkit-keyframes fade-in {
    0% {
      opacity: 0;
    }
    100% {
      opacity: 0.8;
    }
  }
  @keyframes fade-in {
    0% {
      opacity: 0;
    }
    100% {
      opacity: 0.8;
    }
  }
  @supports (display: flex) {
    @-webkit-keyframes fade-in {
      0% {
        opacity: 0;
      }
      100% {
        opacity: 1;
      }
    }
    @keyframes fade-in {
      0% {
        opacity: 0;
      }
      100% {
        opacity: 1;
      }
    }
  }
}
@-webkit-keyframes fade-in {
  0% {
    opacity: 0;
  }
  100% {
    opacity: 1;
  }
}
@keyframes fade-in {
  0% {
    opacity: 0;
  }
  100% {
    opacity: 1;
  }
}
```
